[Name] FAM
[Summary] An API that can be used to find out when a file or directory has changed.
[License] GNU General Public License (GPL)
[Description] FAM, the File Alteration Monitor, provides an API which applications can use to be notified when specific files or directories are changed. It comes in two parts: fam, the daemon which listens for requests and delivers notification, and libfam, a library which client applications can use to communicate with fam.
[Homepage] http://oss.sgi.com/projects/fam/
